{
  "texts": [
    "The 'fundamental description' produced by putting, for example, (A) in the passive voice is not obviously a description of an action.",
    "As both Anscombe and Davidson stress, someone's arm can move without her intentionally moving it.",
    "This is why the movement allegedly requires qualification in terms of something else -an intention or basic reason -to count as something the agent does.",
    "Meanwhile, the straightforward or \"elementary\" causal order that, on the standard story's telling, connects (A) to (E) is only legible when each item in the series is a passive construction.",
    "While the movement of the arm causes the pump to operate, the man's moving his arm doesn't cause his operating the pump, his replenishing the cistern, or his poisoning of the politicianshis moving his arm in the circumstances described constitutes his doing these things."
  ]
}